+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01D6QbCM2ifAAdQdiuHyE8gP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Phase 2: Named Queues\n     2→\n     3→Extend the system to support multiple independent queues, each identified by a name.\n     4→\n     5→## Requirements\n     6→\n     7→- Tasks are added to a specific named queue. If no name is given, a default queue is used.\n     8→- Each named queue operates independently -- adding to one does not affect another.\n     9→- Retrieving a task pulls from the specified queue only.\n    10→- Creating a queue happens implicitly when a task is first added to it.\n    11→- There should be a way to list all queue names that exist.\n    12→- Asking for a task from a non-existent or empty queue returns `null`.\n    13→- The API should remain backward-compatible with Phase 1 (omitting the queue name uses the default).\n    14→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_016oGSzfSbKnK6PH5X37TCqn","session_id":"469ec06b-c50f-485d-b15e-988b43ea0527","uuid":"2dd38e1d-2cfe-44f6-8dfa-ab8da43cc06f"}
