+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BKF5pXUua96n1Y8YCUSBCH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01D3wv8u4jV3b8ATs9UWFQRa","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-task-queue-system.md","content":"# Task Queue System Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a fully-featured in-memory task queue system with 12 phases of increasing sophistication.\n\n**Architecture:** Single `TaskQueue` class as the main entry point, with internal data structures for queues, tasks, DLQ, schedules, and middleware. All state is in-memory using Maps and arrays. The system uses a unified task model that evolves across phases.\n\n**Tech Stack:** TypeScript 5.4, Vitest 2.0, ESLint, Node.js ES2022\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n- `src/index.ts` - Main export file, re-exports everything\n- `src/TaskQueue.ts` - Core TaskQueue class with all methods\n- `src/types.ts` - All TypeScript interfaces and types\n- `src/utils.ts` - Utility functions (ID generation, cron parsing)\n- `tests/phase-01.test.ts` through `tests/phase-12.test.ts` - Tests per phase\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Project Setup & Phase 1 - Basic FIFO Queue\n\n**Files:**\n- Create: `src/types.ts`\n- Create: `src/utils.ts`\n- Create: `src/TaskQueue.ts`\n- Create: `src/index.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-01.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Create types**\n\n```typescript\n// src/types.ts\nexport type TaskStatus = 'pending' | 'processing' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'cancelled';\n\nexport interface Task<T = unknown> {\n  id: string;\n  status: TaskStatus;\n  payload: T;\n  createdAt: Date;\n  queue: string;\n  priority: number;\n  availableAt: Date;\n  attempts: number;\n  maxRetries: number;\n  backoffMs: number;\n  error?: string;\n  dependencies: string[];\n  progress: number;\n  progressMessage?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface TaskOptions {\n  queue?: string;\n  priority?: number;\n  delay?: number;\n  availableAt?: Date;\n  maxRetries?: number;\n  backoffMs?: number;\n  dependencies?: string[];\n}\n```\n\n**Step 2: Create utils**\n\n```typescript\n// src/utils.ts\nlet counter = 0;\nexport function generateId(): string {\n  return `task_${Date.now()}_${++counter}_${Math.random().toString(36).slice(2, 8)}`;\n}\n```\n\n**Step 3: Create TaskQueue class with add/process/size**\n\nCore methods: `add(payload, options?)`, `process(queue?)`, `size(queue?)`\n\n**Step 4: Create index.ts re-exports**\n\n**Step 5: Write phase-01 tests**\n\nTests covering:\n- Add task returns task object with id, status, payload, createdAt\n- New tasks start as pending\n- Process returns oldest pending task in FIFO order\n- Process transitions task to processing\n- Process returns null when empty\n- Size returns count of pending tasks\n- Multiple tasks processed in order\n\n**Step 6: Run tests, build, lint**\n\n```bash\nnpm test -- tests/phase-01.test.ts\nnpm run build\nnpm run lint\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Phase 2 - Named Queues\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-02.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Extend TaskQueue**\n\n- `add()` accepts `queue` option, defaults to `'default'`\n- `process(queue?)` pulls from specified queue\n- `size(queue?)` counts for specified queue\n- `getQueues()` returns list of queue names\n- Internal storage: `Map<string, Task[]>`\n\n**Step 2: Write tests**\n\n- Add to default queue when no name given\n- Add to named queue\n- Queues are independent\n- List queue names\n- Process from non-existent queue returns null\n- Backward compatible with phase 1\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Phase 3 - Priority\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-03.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Add priority support**\n\n- `add()` accepts `priority` option (1-10, default 5)\n- Validate priority range, throw on invalid\n- `process()` returns highest-priority (lowest number) task first\n- Same priority = FIFO\n- Task object exposes priority\n\n**Step 2: Write tests**\n\n- Default priority is 5\n- Higher priority (lower number) processed first\n- Same priority = FIFO\n- Invalid priority throws error\n- Priority is per-queue\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Phase 4 - Delayed Tasks\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts`\n- Modify: `src/types.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-04.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Add delay/availableAt support**\n\n- `add()` accepts `delay` (ms) or `availableAt` (Date)\n- Task stores `availableAt`\n- `process()` skips tasks where `availableAt > now`\n- Order: available non-delayed first, then by availableAt, then priority, then FIFO\n\n**Step 2: Write tests**\n\n- Delayed task not returned before delay\n- Delayed task returned after delay\n- Non-delayed preferred over not-yet-available\n- Multiple delayed tasks ordered correctly\n- Works with named queues\n- Task exposes availableAt\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Phase 5 - Retry with Backoff\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts`\n- Modify: `src/types.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-05.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Add complete/fail methods**\n\n- `complete(taskId)` - marks processing task as completed\n- `fail(taskId, error?)` - marks as failed, re-enqueues with backoff if retries remain\n- Backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)`\n- Track attempts on task\n- Default maxRetries=3, backoffMs=1000\n\n**Step 2: Write tests**\n\n- Complete marks task as completed\n- Fail with retries remaining re-enqueues with delay\n- Exponential backoff timing\n- Configurable retries and backoff\n- Exhausted retries = failed state\n- Retried tasks keep queue and priority\n- Attempt count tracked\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Phase 6 - Dead Letter Queue\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-06.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Add DLQ support**\n\n- When retries exhausted, move to DLQ\n- `getDeadLetterTasks(queue?)` - view DLQ tasks\n- `requeue(taskId)` - move DLQ task back to original queue\n- `clearDeadLetterQueue(queue?)` - clear DLQ\n- Each queue has independent DLQ\n- Tasks retain error info and failure count\n\n**Step 2: Write tests**\n\n- Failed task with no retries goes to DLQ\n- View DLQ tasks\n- DLQ tasks retain error and failure count\n- Requeue from DLQ\n- Clear DLQ\n- Independent DLQs per queue\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Phase 7 - Task Dependencies\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-07.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Add dependency support**\n\n- `add()` accepts `dependencies: string[]`\n- Blocked tasks not returned by `process()`\n- On `complete()`, check if any tasks are unblocked\n- Detect circular dependencies at creation\n- Error on non-existent dependency\n- Failed dependency does NOT fail dependents\n- `getDependencyStatus(taskId)` - inspect dependency status\n\n**Step 2: Write tests**\n\n- Task with dependencies is blocked\n- Task unblocked when all deps complete\n- Circular dependency rejected\n- Non-existent dependency errors\n- Failed dep keeps dependents blocked\n- Dependency status inspection\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Phase 8 - Concurrency Control\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-08.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Add concurrency limits**\n\n- `setConcurrency(queue, limit)` - set max concurrent\n- `getConcurrency(queue)` - get limit\n- `getActiveCount(queue)` - count processing tasks\n- `process()` returns null if at limit\n- Complete/fail frees slot\n- Default: unlimited\n\n**Step 2: Write tests**\n\n- Default unlimited concurrency\n- Set/get concurrency limit\n- Returns null at limit even with pending tasks\n- Completing frees slot\n- Failing frees slot\n- Works with priority ordering\n- Active count tracking\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Phase 9 - Progress & Cancellation\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts`\n- Modify: `src/types.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-09.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Add progress tracking**\n\n- `reportProgress(taskId, percent, message?)` - report 0-100%\n- `getProgress(taskId)` - get current progress\n- `onProgress(taskId, callback)` - subscribe, returns unsubscribe fn\n\n**Step 2: Add cancellation**\n\n- `cancel(taskId)` - cancel pending or processing task\n- Cancelled pending removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing updates status\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n**Step 3: Write tests**\n\n- Report and query progress\n- Progress subscriptions\n- Unsubscribe works\n- Cancel pending task\n- Cancel processing task\n- Cancelled task not retried\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Phase 10 - Recurring Tasks\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts`\n- Modify: `src/types.ts`\n- Modify: `src/utils.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-10.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Add cron parsing to utils**\n\nParse simple cron expressions: `*/N * * * *`, `0 * * * *`, `0 0 * * *`\n\n**Step 2: Add schedule management**\n\n- `addSchedule(id, cronExpr, queue, payload, options?)` - create schedule\n- `removeSchedule(id)` - remove schedule\n- `getSchedules()` - list active schedules\n- `tick(now?)` - check schedules and enqueue due tasks\n\n**Step 3: Write tests**\n\n- Create schedule\n- Remove schedule\n- List schedules\n- Tick enqueues due tasks\n- Removed schedule doesn't create tasks\n- Recurring tasks are regular tasks\n- Every-N-minutes pattern\n- Hourly/daily patterns\n\n---\n\n### Task 11: Phase 11 - Middleware Pipeline\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts`\n- Modify: `src/types.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-11.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Add middleware and handler registration**\n\n- `use(queue, middlewareFn)` - register middleware\n- `setHandler(queue, handlerFn)` - register processing handler\n- `processWithMiddleware(queue)` - process task through pipeline\n\n**Step 2: Write tests**\n\n- Middleware runs in order\n- Middleware can modify task\n- Middleware not calling next skips processing\n- Middleware error fails task\n- Handler runs after middleware\n- Independent middleware per queue\n\n---\n\n### Task 12: Phase 12 - Graceful Shutdown\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `src/TaskQueue.ts`\n- Create: `tests/phase-12.test.ts`\n\n**Step 1: Add shutdown support**\n\n- `shutdown(options?)` - returns Promise with summary\n- After shutdown, `add()` throws error\n- Waits for processing tasks up to timeout\n- Force-cancels on timeout\n- `onShutdown(callback)` - register shutdown callback\n- Multiple calls return same promise\n- Summary: completed, forceCancelled, duration\n\n**Step 2: Write tests**\n\n- Shutdown stops accepting tasks\n- Waits for processing tasks\n- Force-cancels on timeout\n- Shutdown callbacks\n- Multiple shutdown calls safe\n- Immediate shutdown if no processing tasks\n- Summary includes correct counts\n\n---\n\n### Task 13: Final Validation\n\n**Step 1: Run all tests**\n```bash\nnpm test\n```\n\n**Step 2: Build**\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\n**Step 3: Lint**\n```bash\nnpm run lint\n```\n\n**Step 4: Fix any remaining issues**\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":120,"cache_read_input_tokens":24512,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":120},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"469ec06b-c50f-485d-b15e-988b43ea0527","uuid":"08200567-ded3-4bad-bf6d-bc41e15130a5"}
