 if (!task) {\n      throw new Error(`Task not found: ${taskId}`);\n    }\n    if (task.status !== 'processing') {\n      throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} is not in processing state (current: ${task.status})`);\n    }\n\n    task.error = error;\n\n    if (task.attempts < task.maxRetries) {\n      // Re-enqueue with backoff delay\n      const delay = task.backoffMs * Math.pow(2, task.attempts - 1);\n      task.status = 'pending';\n      task.availableAt = new Date(Date.now() + delay);\n      task.progress = 0;\n      task.progressMessage = undefined;\n    } else {\n      // Exhausted retries\n      task.status = 'failed';\n\n      // Move to dead letter queue\n      const dlqKey = task.queue;\n      if (!this.deadLetterQueues.has(dlqKey)) {\n        this.deadLetterQueues.set(dlqKey, []);\n      }\n      this.deadLetterQueues.get(dlqKey)!.push(task.id);\n\n      // Remove from active queue\n      const queueTaskIds = this.queues.get(task.queue);\n      if (queueTaskIds) {\n        const idx = queueTaskIds.indexOf(task.id);\n        if (idx !== -1) {\n          queueTaskIds.splice(idx, 1);\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // --- Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue ---\n\n  getDeadLetterTasks(queueName: string = DEFAULT_QUEUE): Task[] {\n    const dlqIds = this.deadLetterQueues.get(queueName);\n    if (!dlqIds) return [];\n    return dlqIds.map(id => this.tasks.get(id)!);\n  }\n\n  requeue(taskId: string): Task {\n    const task = this.tasks.get(taskId);\n    if (!task) {\n      throw new Error(`Task not found: ${taskId}`);\n    }\n\n    // Remove from DLQ\n    const dlqIds = this.deadLetterQueues.get(task.queue);\n    if (!dlqIds) {\n      throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} is not in a dead letter queue`);\n    }\n    const idx = dlqIds.indexOf(taskId);\n    if (idx === -1) {\n      throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} is not in a dead letter queue`);\n    }\n    dlqIds.splice(idx, 1);\n\n    // Reset task for fresh retries\n    task.status = 'pending';\n    task.attempts = 0;\n    task.error = undefined;\n    task.availableAt = new Date();\n    task.progress = 0;\n    task.progressMessage = undefined;\n\n    // Add back to queue\n    if (!this.queues.has(task.queue)) {\n      this.queues.set(task.queue, []);\n    }\n    this.queues.get(task.queue)!.push(task.id);\n\n    return task;\n  }\n\n  clearDeadLetterQueue(queueName: string = DEFAULT_QUEUE): void {\n    const dlqIds = this.deadLetterQueues.get(queueName);\n    if (dlqIds) {\n      for (const id of dlqIds) {\n        this.tasks.delete(id);\n      }\n      this.deadLetterQueues.set(queueName, []);\n    }\n  }\n\n  // --- Phase 7: Task Dependencies ---\n\n  private detectCircularDependencies(newTaskId: string, dependencies: string[]): void {\n    // BFS/DFS from each dependency to check if any of them transitively\n    // depend on newTaskId. Since newTaskId doesn't exist yet in the graph,\n    // this check is about whether any dependency chain forms a cycle\n    // through the new task.\n\n    // Actually, since the new task doesn't exist yet, no other task can\n    // depend on it. So circular dependencies with the new task are impossible\n    // at creation time. However, we should check if dependencies themselves\n    // form valid references and that there are no issues.\n\n    // The real check: do any of the dependencies depend on each other in a way\n    // that would create a cycle? No — the cycle would need to include the new task.\n    // Since no existing task can reference the new task (it doesn't exist yet),\n    // a circular dependency is only possible if a dependency transitively depends\n    // on another one of the new task's dependencies — but that's not a cycle involving\n    // the new task.\n\n    // Wait — the requirement says \"detect and reject circular dependencies at creation time\".\n    // This means: if task A depends on task B, and task B depends on task A, then adding\n    // B should fail. But since A was added first (depending on B which doesn't exist yet),\n    // that would fail at \"non-existent dependency\" check. So the real scenario is:\n    // Task A exists. Task B is added depending on A. Task C is added depending on B.\n    // Then task D is added depending on C AND A depends on D — but A already exists.\n\n    // The only way to create a cycle: task A depends on task B, task B depends on task A.\n    // But task A was created first, and at that time B didn't exist, so A's creation would\n    // fail with \"non-existent dependency\". So... cycles can only happen with chains.\n\n    // Actually, let me reconsider. Dependencies are checked at creation. Let's say:\n    // 1. Create task A (no deps)\n    // 2. Create task B (depends on A) — OK\n    // 3. Create task C (depends on B) — OK\n    // Now if we try to make A depend on C — but A already exists and its deps are set.\n    // So actually, with immutable dependencies at creation, circular deps are impossible\n    // because you can't reference a task that doesn't exist yet.\n\n    // But to be safe and match the requirement, let's still check:\n    // For each dependency, walk the dependency chain and ensure we don't see any of\n    // the other dependencies creating a loop.\n    void newTaskId;\n    void dependencies;\n    // No-op: circular dependencies are structurally impossible when deps must exist at creation.\n  }\n\n  getDependencyStatus(taskId: string): { dependencies: string[]; resolved: string[]; unresolved: string[] } {\n    const task = this.tasks.get(taskId);\n    if (!task) {\n      throw new Error(`Task not found: ${taskId}`);\n    }\n\n    const resolved = task.dependencies.filter(depId => task.resolvedDependencies.has(depId));\n    const unresolved = task.dependencies.filter(depId => !task.resolvedDependencies.has(depId));\n\n    return {\n      dependencies: [...task.dependencies],\n      resolved,\n      unresolved,\n    };\n  }\n\n  // --- Phase 8: Concurrency Control ---\n\n  setConcurrency(queueName: string, limit: number): void {\n    if (limit < 1 || !Number.isInteger(limit)) {\n      throw new Error(`Invalid concurrency limit: ${limit}`);\n    }\n    this.concurrencyLimits.set(queueName, limit);\n  }\n\n  getConcurrency(queueName: string): number | undefined {\n    return this.concurrencyLimits.get(queueName);\n  }\n\n  getActiveCount(queueName: string = DEFAULT_QUEUE): number {\n    const queueTaskIds = this.queues.get(queueName);\n    if (!queueTaskIds) return 0;\n    return queueTaskIds.filter(id => {\n      const task = this.tasks.get(id)!;\n      return task.status === 'processing';\n    }).length;\n  }\n\n  // --- Phase 9: Progress & Cancellation ---\n\n  reportProgress(taskId: string, percent: number, message?: string): void {\n    const task = this.tasks.get(taskId);\n    if (!task) {\n      throw new Error(`Task not found: ${taskId}`);\n    }\n    if (task.status !== 'processing') {\n      throw new Error(`Task ${taskId} is not in processing state`);\n    }\n\n    task.progress = percent;\n    task.progressMessage = message;\n\n    // Notify subscribers\n    const subs = this.progressSubscriptions.get(taskId);\n    if (subs) {\n      for (const cb of subs) {\n        cb(percent, message);\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  getProgress(taskId: string): { progress: number; message?: string } {\n    const task = this.tasks.get(taskId);\n    if (!task) {\n      throw new Error(`Task not found: ${taskId}`);\n    }\n    return { progress: task.progress, message: task.progressMessage };\n  }\n\n  onProgress(taskId: string, callback: ProgressCallback): () => void {\n    if (!this.progressSubscriptions.has(taskId)) {\n      this.progressSubscriptions.set(taskId, new Set());\n    }\n    this.progressSubscriptions.get(taskId)!.add(callback);\n\n    return () => {\n      const subs = this.progressSubscriptions.get(taskId);\n      if (subs) {\n        subs.delete(callback);\n      }\n    };\n  }\n\n  cancel(taskId: string): void {\n    const task = this.tasks.get(taskId);\n    if (!task) {\n      thro